# PLAN-118 D5 / AC-B8 surface (S179 2026-05-28) — exclude the framework's
# own plan artifacts from the adopter-shipped npm tarball. The plan tree
# is meta-repo internal state (debate transcripts, ceremony receipts,
# ~4.3 GB of PLAN-112 sandbox project-clones); shipping it bloats the
# tarball + carries 500+ stale `_lib/audit_emit.py` copies that adopters'
# Codex tooling or sloppy `sys.path.insert` refactors could plausibly
# inject onto the live producer's sys.path — the exact pollution vector
# PLAN-118 closes via AC-B4/B5/B6/B7. install.sh provisions the canonical
# SCHEMA + examples directly; nothing under .claude/plans/PLAN-* is read
# by adopter runtime. Note: install-npm.sh and the npm-publish workflow
# remain kernel-guarded; this is a NON-KERNEL hygiene fix that closes
# the recurrence vector at the tarball boundary.
.claude/plans/

# PLAN-120-FOLLOWUP WS-D (E4-F1/E4-F2, S185 readiness audit) — exclude the
# framework's OWN test harness from the adopter-shipped npm tarball. The
# _lib/ runtime modules ship (adopter hooks import them), but the test
# files MUST NOT: _lib/tests/ runs framework unit tests that emit real
# audit events without the WS-A session redirect (no conftest ships), and
# test_isolation.py / testing.py do `import pytest` at module top — both
# pollute the adopter's live audit chain and pull a pytest dep an adopter
# need not have. install.sh::install_lib_selective() excludes these at
# COPY time; this .npmignore entry closes the same vector at the tarball
# boundary (defense-in-depth — neither layer alone is fail-closed).
.claude/hooks/_lib/tests/
.claude/hooks/_lib/test_isolation.py
.claude/hooks/_lib/testing.py
